// EFFECTIVE UNTIL JUNE 30, 2015 PER CHAPTERS 280 AND 281 OF 2011 //
A debt settlement services agreement shall:
Be signed and dated by the registrant and the consumer; and
Include, in at least 12 point type:
The name, address, and telephone number of the consumer;
The name, address, and telephone number of the registrant;
A description of the debt settlement services to be provided to the consumer;
The identity of each individual creditor or debt collector whose debts are included in the debt settlement services agreement and the principal amount of the debt owed to each individual creditor or debt collector;
The principal amount of the total debt included in the debt settlement services agreement;
A good faith estimate of the amount of time necessary to achieve the represented results;
To the extent that the debt settlement services may include a debt settlement offer to any of the consumer's creditors or debt collectors, a good faith estimate of:
A statement that:
If the registrant requests or requires the consumer to deposit funds in a dedicated account, a statement that:
A statement that the consumer may be required to pay taxes on the amount by which the consumer's debt is reduced.
The disclosures required under subsection (a)(2)(vii) through (xi) of this section shall be provided to the consumer in a clear and conspicuous manner in the debt settlement services agreement.
